			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">lynxsolaris wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I still have blocks (the first block image in my chr file) that tiles the entire screen.</div>
<br />
<br />That's because most emulators initialize RAM to contain all zeros. Be careful, though - on the real hardware, RAM is initialized to mostly <strong>random</strong> values, so you need to initialize ALL memory you use - for the PPU, this means setting the VRAM address to $2000 and then writing $00/$FF 960 times to $2007 (followed by 64 bytes of $00) and making sure that tile 00/FF is "blank".</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
<br />P.S. If you don't get this note, let me know and I'll write you another.</div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

